WEBVTT

00:03.294 --> 00:05.756
[ "RAISING HANDS RAISING HELL
RAISE 'EM HIGH" PLAYS ]

00:05.756 --> 00:08.129
[ CAR APPROACHING ]

00:08.129 --> 00:10.391
ARE YOU SURE
YOU SHOULD DO THAT HERE?

00:10.391 --> 00:12.633
♪ THIS BODY ISN'T MINE,
BUT I GOT A HEART OF GOLD ♪
WE'RE AWFULLY CLOSE
TO THE ROAD.

00:12.633 --> 00:14.225
WHAT ARE YOU SO WORRIED
ABOUT?

00:14.225 --> 00:16.227
♪ AND I'M SITTING IN A DESK ♪
WHAT WE'RE DOING
IS ILLEGAL.

00:16.227 --> 00:18.729
♪ NAILED TO THE FLOOR ♪
I JUST DON'T LIKE DOING THINGS
THAT ARE ILLEGAL.

00:18.729 --> 00:21.312
♪ DOING EVERYTHING I'M TOLD ♪
WELL, SO WE JUST --
JUST DUMP THEM ON THE GROUND?

00:21.312 --> 00:23.604
NO, YOU --
YOU KNOW, WE...SCATTER THEM.

00:23.604 --> 00:25.276
♪ DOING EVERYTHING I'M TOLD ♪

00:25.276 --> 00:27.278
AROUND THE CAMPSITE.

00:27.278 --> 00:28.279
[ GRUNTS ]

00:28.279 --> 00:29.530
THIS IS OUR SPOT.

00:29.530 --> 00:31.532
♪ YOU DRAGGED ME TO THE DOCTOR ♪

00:31.532 --> 00:33.654
♪ AND YOU DIDN'T TELL ME WHY ♪

00:33.654 --> 00:36.157
♪ A NINE-YEAR-OLD
IN HEADPHONES ♪
OKAY, POPS.
IT'S SHOW TIME.

00:36.157 --> 00:38.709
♪ RAISING HANDS, RAISING HELL,
RAISE 'EM HIGH ♪
Meredith: EVERYBODY HAS
SOMETHING TO HIDE.

00:38.709 --> 00:41.041
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

00:41.041 --> 00:44.085
♪ OH, YOU BETTER
RAISE 'EM HIGH ♪
WE CAN'T JUST EXPOSE
ALL OUR SECRETS TO THE WORLD.

00:44.085 --> 00:45.426
Jo: IT'S ON TOP SHELF!
IN THE FRIDGE.
OH!

00:45.426 --> 00:47.718
HELLO -- I'M IN HERE.
OH, I KNOW. I'M SORRY.

00:47.718 --> 00:50.050
♪ OO-HOO ♪
OUR SHOWER'S STILL BUSTED
AND I GOT ROUNDS.

00:50.050 --> 00:52.473
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I TOLD HIM A THOUSAND TIMES...

00:52.473 --> 00:54.345
♪ YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW,
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW ♪
...YOU PUT THE BREAD
ON THE COUNTER, IT MOLDS.

00:54.345 --> 00:56.267
♪ OO-HOO ♪
YOU PUT IT IN THE FRIDGE,
IT'S FINE.

00:56.267 --> 00:58.139
♪ YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW,
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW ♪
I'M RIGHT, RIGHT?

00:58.139 --> 01:00.311
♪ OO-HOO ♪
OKAY. WHEW!

01:00.311 --> 01:03.484
♪ SAY, YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW,
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW ♪
HEY, DO YOU KNOW
WHERE THE BREAD IS?

01:03.484 --> 01:05.146
♪ OO-HOO ♪
YOU NEED TO
GET YOUR SHOWER FIXED!

01:05.146 --> 01:06.487
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
THAT'S HOW WE GET HURT.

01:06.487 --> 01:08.109
♪ HEY! ♪
IT'S HOW WE RISK
HURTING OTHER PEOPLE.

01:08.109 --> 01:11.192
WE HAVE TO DECIDE
HOW MUCH WE LET OUT...

01:11.192 --> 01:13.904
♪ HEY! ♪
...AND KEEP THE TRUTH
TO OURSELVES.

01:13.904 --> 01:15.616
HEY. HOW'D IT GO
WITH THE KIDS?

01:15.616 --> 01:17.037
UH, GREAT.
UH, THEY'RE AMAZING.

01:17.037 --> 01:18.329
I JUST DROPPED THEM OFF
AT DAYCARE.

01:18.329 --> 01:19.830
THANKS AGAIN
FOR WATCHING THEM.

01:19.830 --> 01:21.502
YEAH.
HOW ABOUT YOU?

01:21.502 --> 01:24.545
HOW WAS YOUR WEEKEND...
IN D.C...

01:24.545 --> 01:26.046
WITH YOUR HUSBAND?

01:27.168 --> 01:29.170
IT...WAS FUN.

01:29.170 --> 01:31.922
UH -- UH, I'M A LITTLE
EXHAUSTED, YOU KNOW.

01:31.922 --> 01:34.595
BUT IT WAS THE GOOD KIND
OF EXHAUSTED, RIGHT?

01:34.595 --> 01:35.926
[ BUTTON CLICKS ]
DID YOU EVEN LEAVE
THE BEDROOM?

01:35.926 --> 01:38.098
WAS HE SURPRISED?
DID HE FREAK?

01:38.098 --> 01:40.521
YEAH, DID HE...FREAK?

01:40.521 --> 01:41.812
OR DID YOU JUST
GO STRAIGHT

01:41.812 --> 01:43.184
TO GETTING
[singsong voice] FREA-KAY?

01:43.184 --> 01:45.646
YOU KNOW, DID WE EVEN PUSH
THE BUTTON, BECAUSE IT'S JUST...

01:46.567 --> 01:48.609
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
OH. MM-HMM.

01:48.609 --> 01:50.651
HEY, LOOK WHO'S BACK.

01:51.442 --> 01:53.073
MEREDITH WAS
JUST ABOUT TO TELL US

01:53.073 --> 01:55.946
ABOUT HER WEEKEND
WITH DEREK.

01:55.946 --> 01:57.998
GOOD. TELL ME NOW SO YOU
DON'T SHOW UP IN MY BED TONIGHT.

01:57.998 --> 02:00.120
IT'S A GOOD THING YOU DIDN'T
WALK IN ON THIS MORNING.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.082
[ SIGHS ]
OH.

02:02.082 --> 02:04.245
EVERYONE'S GETTING FREAKY
BUT ME.

02:04.245 --> 02:06.627
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
WELL, ACTUALLY,
I WAS JUST --

02:06.627 --> 02:09.670
ACTUALLY REMEMBERED
I-I HAVE TO, UH -- YEAH.

02:09.670 --> 02:13.013
THEY TOTALLY GOT FREAKY.
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

02:13.013 --> 02:14.755
AND I COME IN
THIS MORNING,

02:14.755 --> 02:17.518
AND HERMAN'S REARRANGED
THE ENTIRE O.R. BOARD

02:17.518 --> 02:19.139
WITH NEW FETAL SURGERIES.

02:19.139 --> 02:21.522
I USED TO BE SO GOOD
AT ONE-NIGHT STANDS.

02:21.522 --> 02:23.644
I...I MISSED A BEAT.

02:23.644 --> 02:25.266
NO,
I WAS GREAT AT THEM.

02:25.266 --> 02:27.978
AND NOW, WHENEVER
I'M NOT WATCHING SOFIA,

02:27.978 --> 02:31.232
I JUST SIT ALONE AT HOME
IN MY PAJAMAS.

02:31.232 --> 02:34.034
I-I WANT TO BE OUT OF MY PAJAMAS
AND NOT ALONE.

02:34.034 --> 02:35.115
SO GO.

02:35.115 --> 02:36.657
MEET SOMEONE.
IT'S EASY.

02:36.657 --> 02:38.158
OH, IT'S EASY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:38.158 --> 02:39.950
WELL, WHAT DO YOU DO?
WHAT'S YOUR LINE?

02:39.950 --> 02:42.243
I DON'T USE LINES.
I'M JUST HONEST.

02:42.243 --> 02:43.874
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
"HONEST"?

02:43.874 --> 02:45.286
[ SCOFFS ]
I DON'T KNOW.

02:45.286 --> 02:47.208
THEY START WITH
"WHAT DO YOU DO?"

02:47.208 --> 02:49.380
AND I TELL THEM
I'M A TRAUMA SURGEON,

02:49.380 --> 02:52.423
AND THEY WONDER
WHY I CHOSE THAT.

02:52.423 --> 02:55.466
AND I TELL THEM
I SERVED IN THE WAR,

02:55.466 --> 02:58.889
AND I FIXED SOLDIERS
ON THE BATTLEFIELD,

02:58.889 --> 03:01.642
AND THAT WAS A...

03:01.642 --> 03:05.145
REALLY SATISFYING WAY
TO SAVE LIVES.

03:05.145 --> 03:08.018
AND IT STILL IS.

03:08.018 --> 03:10.070
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

03:10.070 --> 03:11.071
YEAH, THAT'LL DO IT.

03:11.071 --> 03:12.152
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:12.152 --> 03:15.236
AH, YOU'VE GOT GAME,
MAJOR HUNT.

03:15.236 --> 03:16.987
IT'S NOT A GAME.
IT'S JUST --

03:16.987 --> 03:19.780
WHA-- WHAT HAPPENED
TO THE COUCH?

03:19.780 --> 03:21.492
OH.

03:21.492 --> 03:23.454
HEY.

03:24.915 --> 03:26.377
SORRY I'M LATE.
I'M SORRY I'M LATE.

03:26.377 --> 03:28.088
Three surgeries today,
Robbins.

03:28.088 --> 03:29.880
They're not gonna round
on themselves.

03:29.880 --> 03:31.462
I know. I'm on it.

03:31.462 --> 03:34.094
YEAH, UM, WILSON JUST BARGED IN
AND STOLE MY SHOWER.

03:34.094 --> 03:35.886
EDWARDS, DOES SHE ALWAYS
WALK AROUND NAKED?

03:35.886 --> 03:37.097
NOT AROUND THE HOSPITAL,
GENERALLY.

03:37.097 --> 03:39.390
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S LIKE "RESIDENTS GONE WILD."

03:39.390 --> 03:41.682
ROBBINS, DO YOU LIVE
WITH RESIDENTS?

03:41.682 --> 03:43.764
Oh, God.
Is that thing still on?

03:43.764 --> 03:46.186
YOU'RE A GROWN-UP.
GET YOUR OWN PLACE.

03:46.186 --> 03:47.268
I need you focused here.

03:47.268 --> 03:49.059
LIE DOWN, NICOLE.

03:50.230 --> 03:53.153
So, d-did Wilson just climb
in the shower with you?

03:53.153 --> 03:56.567
Yeah. No.
We-- Instead of me.

03:56.567 --> 03:58.859
WAS SHE COMING ON
TO YOU?

03:58.859 --> 03:59.910
No!
Doubtful.

03:59.910 --> 04:01.071
YOU KNOW WHAT?
CAN WE --

04:01.071 --> 04:02.162
[ Laughs ]
JUST --
LET'S DROP IT.

04:02.162 --> 04:05.416
[ Laughing ]
"RESIDENTS GONE WILD."

04:05.416 --> 04:06.417
[ LAUGHS ]

04:06.417 --> 04:07.828
Would you go?

04:07.828 --> 04:09.630
You're making her laugh
too much.

04:09.630 --> 04:10.631
[ Clears throat ]

04:10.631 --> 04:14.375
[ LAUGHING CONTINUES ]

04:14.375 --> 04:16.046
MWAH!

04:16.046 --> 04:19.009
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GOING BACK
TO THE AIRPORT.

04:19.009 --> 04:21.432
I JUST COULDN'T
GET ON THAT PLANE.

04:21.432 --> 04:23.143
THANK YOU.

04:23.143 --> 04:26.146
THANK YOU FOR LETTING ME
STAY THE WEEKEND,

04:26.146 --> 04:28.649
BEING THERE FOR ME.

04:28.649 --> 04:30.150
IT WAS
JUST WHAT I NEEDED.

04:30.150 --> 04:32.152
I HATE THE CIRCUMSTANCES,
BUT, UH,

04:32.152 --> 04:35.856
I'M GLAD IT GAVE US
A CHANCE TO RECONNECT.

04:35.856 --> 04:38.399
I HEAR THAT JACKSON AND APRIL
ARE COMING IN TODAY.

04:38.399 --> 04:40.951
HAVE YOU SEEN HIM?

04:45.035 --> 04:48.038
CATHERINE, HE ASKED YOU
TO KEEP YOUR DISTANCE.

04:48.038 --> 04:50.210
AND I'M HONORING
THAT REQUEST.

04:50.210 --> 04:52.292
LOOK, I KNOW HOW HARD THAT IS
FOR YOU, OKAY?

04:52.292 --> 04:54.174
BUT YOU SENT FOOD,
YOU CALL FOR UPDATES.

04:54.174 --> 04:55.215
THEY KNOW YOU'RE THERE.

04:55.215 --> 04:57.338
I KNOW.
I JUST HATE IT.

04:59.970 --> 05:01.342
I'LL MISS YOU.

05:04.184 --> 05:07.097
WELL, I'LL --
I'LL BE IN THE O.R. ANYWAY.

05:07.097 --> 05:09.640
I HAVE
AN OPEN COLECTOMY TODAY.

05:09.640 --> 05:12.142
I COULD SCRUB IN,
DO YOUR URETERAL STENTS.

05:12.142 --> 05:14.395
THAT'LL GIVE US
A LITTLE MORE TIME.

05:14.395 --> 05:18.028
MM. OH, I COULD
MAKE THAT HAPPEN.

05:18.028 --> 05:19.650
MAKE IT HAPPEN.

05:19.650 --> 05:20.651
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

05:23.113 --> 05:24.995
SO, YOU AND MEREDITH
ARE GETTING PRETTY TIGHT, HUH?

05:26.116 --> 05:27.538
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

05:27.538 --> 05:29.079
WELL, WHAT DID SHE SAY
ABOUT THIS WEEKEND?

05:29.079 --> 05:31.041
WHY?
DID SHE TELL YOU SOMETHING?
YOU SAID SHE TOLD YOU.

05:31.041 --> 05:34.585
UH, NO, I SAID
SHE WAS ABOUT TO TELL ME.

05:34.585 --> 05:35.956
WHAT DO YOU THINK
SHE WAS ABOUT TO TELL YOU?

05:35.956 --> 05:37.127
WHAT DID SHE TELL YOU?

05:39.219 --> 05:40.461
WASN'T THERE
A COUCH THERE?

05:41.632 --> 05:44.014
Miranda: WHAT -- UM, DON'T YOU
WANT TO SAY SOMETHING?

05:44.014 --> 05:46.557
THIS IS THE CLOSEST THING
TO A FUNERAL.

05:46.557 --> 05:48.929
NO,
DAD HATED FUNERALS.

05:48.929 --> 05:51.432
"SPRINKLE ME
IN THE WOODS."

05:51.432 --> 05:52.973
GOD, HE WAS
A PAIN IN THE ASS.

05:53.814 --> 05:55.396
WELL,
YOU CAN'T JUST SAY THAT.

05:58.479 --> 06:00.280
YOU KNOW,
ONE OF HIS FAVORITE MEMORIES

06:00.280 --> 06:01.942
WAS TAKING US OUT HERE
CAMPING.

06:01.942 --> 06:03.904
"WE EAT WHAT WE CATCH."

06:03.904 --> 06:05.155
[ GRUMBLES ]

06:05.155 --> 06:06.537
"WE SLEEP
IN WHAT WE CAN CARRY."

06:06.537 --> 06:07.538
[ LAUGHS ]

06:08.789 --> 06:09.830
JUST US MEN.

06:11.992 --> 06:13.253
YOU OKAY?

06:16.997 --> 06:18.128
MAYBE WE SHOULD JUST GO.

06:19.960 --> 06:21.922
HEY,
RACE YOU TO THE TOP.

06:21.922 --> 06:23.093
WAI-- [ SIGHS ]

06:23.093 --> 06:25.175
COME ON. WHAT YOU GOT?
WHAT YOU GOT?

06:25.175 --> 06:28.098
HMM?

06:28.098 --> 06:29.640
OH, GOODNESS.

06:29.640 --> 06:31.391
HA, HA!

06:31.391 --> 06:33.353
[ LAUGHS ]

06:34.184 --> 06:36.066
[ SIGHS ]

06:36.066 --> 06:37.107
IT'S SO MUGGY.

06:37.107 --> 06:38.228
IT'S HARD TO BREATHE.

06:38.228 --> 06:39.229
YOU OKAY?

06:39.229 --> 06:41.732
HEY, CURT.
YOU SHOULD SIT DOWN.

06:41.732 --> 06:42.903
WHOA! CURT!
CURT!

06:42.903 --> 06:44.114
WHA--

06:44.114 --> 06:45.736
CURT!
[ GRUNTS ]

06:50.410 --> 06:57.668
CALL 911!

07:03.844 --> 07:05.385
HEY.
HOW WAS YOUR WEEKEND?

07:05.385 --> 07:07.177
IT WAS NICE.
SHE GOT SOME.

07:07.177 --> 07:08.388
SHE DOESN'T WANT TO
TALK ABOUT IT.

07:08.388 --> 07:11.181
OH, WELL, I'M GLAD YOU WENT.
I GOT SOME, TOO.

07:11.181 --> 07:13.053
DEFINITELY DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT THAT.

07:13.053 --> 07:14.184
[ SIREN WAILING ]

07:14.184 --> 07:16.607
[ HORN BLARES ]

07:19.059 --> 07:21.401
WHAT DO WE GOT?
CURTIS WARREN, POST SYNCOPE.

07:21.401 --> 07:24.064
31. HE'S STILL TACHYCARDIC,
DIAPHORETIC,

07:24.064 --> 07:25.275
AND HYPOTENSIVE AFTER FAINTING.

07:25.275 --> 07:27.828
BUT DON'T JUST STAND HERE, GREY.
GIVE ME A HAND.

07:27.828 --> 07:29.570
Man: OVER HERE!

07:29.570 --> 07:31.201
HILLARY LIST,
27-YEAR-OLD FEMALE,

07:31.201 --> 07:33.373
FOUND UNCONSCIOUS AT THE SCENE
AFTER A PRETTY BAD TUMBLE

07:33.373 --> 07:35.035
DOWN A FLIGHT OF CONCRETE STAIRS
IN THE PARK.

07:35.035 --> 07:36.206
HILL, HONEY,
I'M RIGHT HERE.

07:36.206 --> 07:37.287
OH, IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

07:37.287 --> 07:38.709
THIS WAS YOUR FAULT?

07:38.709 --> 07:40.841
NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

07:40.841 --> 07:43.844
I DIDN'T PUSH HER.
I PROPOSED TO HER.

07:45.295 --> 07:48.218
OKAY,
LET'S GO TO TRAUMA TWO.

07:48.218 --> 07:49.469
Meredith:
FAST SCAN IS NEGATIVE.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.011
BECAUSE THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH ME.

07:51.011 --> 07:54.054
ANY CHANGES IN YOUR DIET
RECENTLY?

07:54.054 --> 07:56.096
I TOLD THEM
I MISSED BREAKFAST,

07:56.096 --> 07:58.519
SO I WAS A LITTLE WOOZY
IN THE WOODS.

07:58.519 --> 08:00.651
HE'S STILL MILDLY HYPOTENSIVE
AFTER TWO LITERS.

08:00.651 --> 08:02.102
I'M FINE.

08:02.943 --> 08:04.154
[ INHALES SHARPLY ] AAH.

08:04.154 --> 08:06.066
WELL, THERE'S DEFINITELY
SOME TENDERNESS THERE.

08:06.066 --> 08:09.029
WELL, RUN HIS LIVER ENZYMES
AND GET A COAG PANEL.

08:09.029 --> 08:10.280
LET'S GET YOU INTO THIS.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

08:10.280 --> 08:11.992
I'M GONNA RE-CHECK
THAT ABDOM--
NO!

08:11.992 --> 08:13.373
LOOK, I DON'T NEED TO PUT ON
THIS STUPID THING.

08:13.373 --> 08:15.165
WOULD YOU CALM DOWN?
LOOK, BENJI, GET OFF ME!

08:15.165 --> 08:16.667
W-WOULD YOU TELL THEM
TO BACK OFF?

08:16.667 --> 08:19.119
OKAY, OKAY.
OKAY.

08:19.119 --> 08:21.121
FAMILY SHOULDN'T BE
IN HERE ANYWAY.

08:21.121 --> 08:23.003
LET'S STEP OUTSIDE.

08:23.003 --> 08:25.385
YOU CAN CHANGE,
AND I WILL BE BACK FOR YOU.

08:27.087 --> 08:28.088
[ SIGHS ]

08:34.134 --> 08:36.727
HE'S USUALLY A SWEETHEART.
I'LL GO TALK TO HIM.

08:36.727 --> 08:38.559
WELL, BAILEY,
HE'S MY PATIENT.

08:38.559 --> 08:40.400
I'LL TAKE IT.
YOU CAN GO.

08:43.774 --> 08:45.776
Todd:
I TOOK HER TO THE PARK.

08:45.776 --> 08:48.649
IT WAS, UM -- IT WAS
WHERE WE HAD OUR FIRST DATE,

08:48.649 --> 08:51.151
SO I THOUGHT
THAT HAD A CERTAIN SYMMETRY.

08:51.151 --> 08:52.412
I'LL ORDER A HEAD C.T.

08:52.412 --> 08:54.494
AND AN X-RAY FOR HER RIGHT WRIST
AND RIGHT KNEE.

08:54.494 --> 08:57.658
AT THE TOP OF THE STAIRS,
I GOT DOWN ON MY KNEE

08:57.658 --> 09:01.001
AND I SAID...

09:01.001 --> 09:04.004
"HILLARY, WHEN I MET YOU,

09:04.004 --> 09:07.167
"I FELT LIKE MY LIFE BLOSSOMED
WITH FULLNESS."

09:08.589 --> 09:11.722
"LIKE THE SUN HAD SHONE DOWN
ON ME, BABY."

09:13.223 --> 09:14.845
AND THAT'S AS FAR
AS I GOT.

09:14.845 --> 09:18.058
I HAD MORE, BUT SHE FAINTED
AND SHE FELL ALL THE WAY DOWN.

09:18.058 --> 09:20.520
I...SHOULD'VE CAUGHT HER.

09:21.982 --> 09:24.064
HILL? HILL? HILL?
HONEY? HONEY.

09:24.064 --> 09:25.395
HEY, HEY, HEY.
IT'S ME.

09:25.395 --> 09:28.949
RIGHT HERE.
HEY, I'M HERE.

09:28.949 --> 09:30.240
I'M NEVER LEAVING
YOUR SIDE.

09:30.240 --> 09:33.113
I'LL NEVER...
EVER LEAVE YOU.

09:33.113 --> 09:35.035
I'LL NEVER...

09:35.035 --> 09:36.827
[ SIGHS ]

09:36.827 --> 09:39.620
Callie: OH, SHE'S OUT AGAIN.
HILL? HILL?
HILLARY?

09:39.620 --> 09:41.041
TODD, UH,
WE'RE GONNA ADMIT HER NOW.

09:41.041 --> 09:42.542
YEAH.
SO, UH, DR. WILSON'S
GONNA SHOW YOU

09:42.542 --> 09:43.624
WHERE YOU CAN WAIT, OKAY?

09:43.624 --> 09:44.204
AND PAGE NEURO.

09:44.204 --> 09:45.205
I'M HERE.

09:45.205 --> 09:46.416
Jo: TODD.

09:46.416 --> 09:49.049
I'LL JUST...I'M JUST GONNA BE
OVER HERE, BABY.

09:49.049 --> 09:52.262
DR. HERMAN, YOU SCHEDULED
ANOTHER SURGERY FOR TOMORROW?

09:52.262 --> 09:53.383
I THOUGHT WE SAID --

09:53.383 --> 09:56.056
YES, UH, THE LARSEN MOM.
SORRY.

09:59.019 --> 10:01.061
IS THIS
THE ATTENDINGS' LOUNGE COUCH?

10:01.061 --> 10:02.182
IT WAS.

10:02.182 --> 10:05.435
DR. HERMAN, PLEASE STOP
MAKING ME BE THIS GUY.

10:05.435 --> 10:07.357
YOU CAN'T JUST STEAL
HOSPITAL FURNITURE.

10:07.357 --> 10:08.649
I NEED THIS COUCH.

10:08.649 --> 10:10.821
THIS IS THE BEST COUCH
IN THE BUILDING.

10:10.821 --> 10:13.153
IT'S FIRM, BUT SOFT.

10:13.153 --> 10:14.825
BOUNCY.

10:14.825 --> 10:16.827
RESPONSIVE.

10:16.827 --> 10:19.119
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO TRY IT OUT?

10:20.450 --> 10:23.744
WELL, UM...I-I THINK
THAT'S, UM --

10:23.744 --> 10:27.087
I-I-I APPRECIATE
THE, UM, OFFER, BUT I --

10:27.087 --> 10:29.840
UH, HUNT.
I'M MESSING WITH YOU.

10:29.840 --> 10:31.672
LARSEN'S GONNA BE
A QUICK IN AND OUT.

10:31.672 --> 10:32.803
9:30, O.R. SIX.

10:32.803 --> 10:34.054
IS THAT FINE WITH YOU?
THAT'S FINE, YEAH.

10:34.054 --> 10:36.176
AND, UM...

10:36.176 --> 10:38.849
WAS THAT A "NO"
ON TRYING OUT THE COUCH?

10:38.849 --> 10:40.220
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:40.220 --> 10:43.103
[ LAUGHS ]

10:44.064 --> 10:45.856
HEY.
SO, I'M GOOD TO GO?

10:45.856 --> 10:48.819
CURT, YOUR LIVER ENZYMES,
THEY'RE OFF THE CHARTS.

10:48.819 --> 10:50.480
ANY IDEA
WHY THAT MIGHT BE?

10:50.480 --> 10:53.033
I GOT TO REMINISCING ABOUT DAD
LAST NIGHT.

10:53.033 --> 10:54.404
MAYBE ONE TOO MANY
WHISKY TOASTS.

10:54.404 --> 10:56.156
OKAY,
I'M GONNA GET A C.T.

10:56.156 --> 10:57.237
OH, COME ON.

11:00.951 --> 11:02.662
LISTEN.

11:02.662 --> 11:03.954
WHAT ARE YOU GETTING AT?

11:03.954 --> 11:05.165
I RAN SOME EXTRA TESTS,

11:05.165 --> 11:07.878
BECAUSE WHAT I WAS SEEING
WASN'T MAKING ANY SENSE.

11:07.878 --> 11:10.961
YOUR LAB RESULTS FOR A
30-YEAR-OLD MAN ARE NOT NORMAL,

11:10.961 --> 11:13.003
AND YOU HAD THE ESTROGEN LEVELS
OF A YOUNG WOMAN.

11:15.345 --> 11:18.098
I JUST WANT TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DEALING WITH
SO I CAN HELP YOU.

11:20.721 --> 11:22.682
HILLARY,
SCANS SHOW THAT THE FALL

11:22.682 --> 11:25.225
CAUSED AN ARTERY
UNDER YOUR SKULL TO BLEED.

11:25.225 --> 11:28.108
YOU'LL NEED SURGERY
TO REPAIR IT.

11:28.108 --> 11:30.190
AND THEN DR. WILSON
AND I WILL REPAIR THE
FRACTURE IN YOUR KNEE.

11:30.190 --> 11:32.442
BUT NONE OF THIS EXPLAINS
WHY YOU PASSED OUT.

11:32.442 --> 11:33.734
HAS THIS
EVER HAPPENED BEFORE?

11:33.734 --> 11:36.156
FAINTING, DIZZY SPELLS?
NO, NEVER.

11:36.156 --> 11:39.029
UH, TODD SAID THAT IT HAPPENED
A COUPLE OF TIMES.

11:39.029 --> 11:41.201
YOU WERE TALKING ON THE COUCH
AND THEN YOU --

11:41.201 --> 11:42.622
I JUST NODDED OFF.

11:42.622 --> 11:45.495
WELL, I'D LIKE TO RUN A COMPLETE
NEURO WORK-UP TO FIND OUT --

11:45.495 --> 11:46.496
IS THAT REALLY NECESSARY?

11:46.496 --> 11:47.998
I KNOW IT'S SCARY,

11:47.998 --> 11:50.130
BUT MULTIPLE FAINTING SPELLS
CAN MEAN A LOT OF THINGS --

11:50.130 --> 11:51.211
HEART PROBLEMS --
IT'S NOT THAT.

11:51.211 --> 11:52.923
I'M ALSO CONCERNED
ABOUT NARCOLEPSY, CATAPLEXY --

11:52.923 --> 11:55.425
NO, NO!
THERE'S NO PLEXIES.

11:55.425 --> 11:56.716
I DIDN'T FAINT.

11:56.716 --> 11:58.468
NOT ON THE COUCH,
NOT ON THE STAIRS.

11:58.468 --> 12:01.181
OKAY, WELL,
TODD SAID THAT --

12:01.181 --> 12:02.722
I FAKED IT.

12:02.722 --> 12:04.304
I FAKED FAINTING
WHEN HE PROPOSED

12:04.304 --> 12:07.057
BECAUSE I DIDN'T KNOW
HOW TO SAY NO

12:07.057 --> 12:10.190
WITHOUT BREAKING HIS TENDER,
LITTLE, QUIVERING HEART.

12:12.352 --> 12:13.944
WHOA.

12:16.236 --> 12:18.859
WE SHOULD SCRUB IN TOGETHER
MORE OFTEN.

12:18.859 --> 12:21.411
I COULD COME TO YOU
ON OCCASION.

12:21.411 --> 12:25.665
I'M THINKING HE WILL NEED
A COMPONENT SEPARATION.

12:25.665 --> 12:27.537
I'LL CALL IN
A PLASTICS CONSULT.

12:27.537 --> 12:29.539
NO, HE'S FINE.
THERE'S HARDLY ANY --

12:29.539 --> 12:31.832
PAGE DR. AVERY, PLEASE.
UH-HUH. YOU GOT IT.

12:31.832 --> 12:34.134
Curt: IF THERE'S GOOD NEWS
AND BAD NEWS,

12:34.134 --> 12:36.176
I WANT
THE GOOD NEWS FIRST.

12:36.176 --> 12:37.427
OKAY.

12:37.427 --> 12:39.679
THE GOOD NEWS IS, A PERSON
CAN LIVE WITHOUT A SPLEEN.

12:39.679 --> 12:41.221
OH.

12:41.221 --> 12:42.722
WOW.

12:42.722 --> 12:44.144
I'M REMOVING YOURS TODAY.

12:44.144 --> 12:47.097
THE C.T. SHOWED YOUR SPLEEN
IS REMARKABLY SWOLLEN.

12:47.097 --> 12:49.229
IT'S PROBABLY DUE TO A CLOT
IN THE SPLENIC VEIN --

12:49.229 --> 12:50.020
ARE YOU ON DRUGS?

12:50.020 --> 12:52.062
COKE OR SOMETHING?
BENJI, COME ON.

12:52.062 --> 12:53.653
'CAUSE I'M LOOKING
AT THIS ORGAN DAMAGE

12:53.653 --> 12:54.734
AND I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO THINK.

12:56.156 --> 12:58.488
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT IT COULD BE, DR. GREY?

13:00.780 --> 13:01.781
OKAY.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.533
CURT.

13:03.533 --> 13:04.664
DON'T BE STUPID.

13:04.664 --> 13:06.786
ALL RIGHT,
IF YOU'RE IN TROUBLE,

13:06.786 --> 13:08.959
YOU CAN TELL ME,
WHATEVER IT IS.

13:08.959 --> 13:10.370
YOU KNOW THAT.

13:10.370 --> 13:11.371
BEN.

13:11.371 --> 13:13.413
YOU KNOW ME.

13:13.413 --> 13:15.125
I DON'T DO DRUGS.

13:15.125 --> 13:17.547
I NEVER HAVE.

13:20.220 --> 13:21.721
[ SIGHS ]

13:21.721 --> 13:22.923
CAN YOU MAKE THAT CALL?

13:22.923 --> 13:24.184
HE WOULDN'T LIE TO ME.

13:24.184 --> 13:25.846
DRUGS ARE OFF THE TABLE.

13:25.846 --> 13:27.017
BUT IT'S SOMETHING,

13:27.017 --> 13:29.479
SO TRY THINKING LIKE A DOCTOR,
NOT HIS --

13:29.479 --> 13:31.191
I AM THINKING
LIKE A DOCTOR.

13:31.191 --> 13:32.602
MAYBE THERE'S
A GENETIC COMPONENT.

13:32.602 --> 13:34.064
MY FATHER JUST DIED
OF COLON CANCER.

13:34.064 --> 13:35.315
MAYBE WE START THERE.

13:35.315 --> 13:37.027
I DON'T THINK
IT'S HIS COLON.

13:37.027 --> 13:38.568
YOU GOT A BETTER IDEA?

13:38.568 --> 13:40.991
ALL RIGHT,
THEN WE START RUNNING TESTS.

13:40.991 --> 13:43.203
LOOK, I JUST LOST MY DAD,
MIRANDA.

13:43.203 --> 13:45.075
I'M NOT GONNA LOSE
MY BROTHER, TOO.

13:45.075 --> 13:46.076
MM-HMM.

13:46.076 --> 13:48.618
JUST --

13:55.215 --> 13:57.087
OKAY, IS THIS
WHAT I THINK IT IS?

13:57.087 --> 13:58.418
WHAT DO YOU THINK IT IS?

13:58.418 --> 13:59.669
I'M NOT BLIND, GREY.

13:59.669 --> 14:01.261
MY HUSBAND MIGHT BE,
BUT I'M NOT.

14:01.261 --> 14:04.925
NOW, HE HAS NO HAIR
ON HIS CHEST OR ARMS.

14:04.925 --> 14:06.806
HE WAXES HIS EYEBROWS.

14:06.806 --> 14:08.268
I'D KILL
TO HAVE EYEBROWS LIKE THAT.

14:08.268 --> 14:11.311
AND THEN I'M LOOKING AT THESE
NUMBERS AND THE SPLENIC DAMAGE,

14:11.311 --> 14:13.974
IS HE DOING
WHAT I THINK HE'S DOING?

14:13.974 --> 14:15.815
YOU HAVE TO ASK CURT.

14:23.073 --> 14:24.694
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

14:24.694 --> 14:27.867
Woman: NURSES' STATION.

14:31.701 --> 14:34.124
THAT ZOLA, SHE COULD PLAY
GO FISH ALL NIGHT LONG.

14:34.124 --> 14:36.496
YOU HAVE A BUDDING CARD SHARK
ON YOUR HANDS.

14:36.496 --> 14:37.707
[ LAUGHS ]

14:37.707 --> 14:39.259
YEAH, WELL,
WE EVENTUALLY HIDE THE CARDS.

14:39.259 --> 14:41.131
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
SHE'LL STOP.

14:41.131 --> 14:43.173
I'LL HAVE TO REMEMBER THAT
FOR NEXT TIME.

14:43.173 --> 14:47.097
LOOK, I JUST WANT TO SAY
THAT, UM...

14:47.097 --> 14:50.720
I AM NOT HERE TO JUDGE YOU,
BUT I'M A BAD LIAR.

14:50.720 --> 14:52.772
SO...
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

14:52.772 --> 14:55.105
YOU PACKED A SUITCASE
FULL OF LINGERIE

14:55.105 --> 14:57.187
AND YOU WENT AWAY
FOR THE WEEKEND.

14:57.187 --> 14:58.518
YEAH, I --

14:58.518 --> 15:00.150
AND THEN DEREK CALLED ME
THREE TIMES

15:00.150 --> 15:01.982
ASKING WHERE YOU WERE.

15:01.982 --> 15:03.153
MEANWHILE, YOU TEXTED ME

15:03.153 --> 15:04.945
TELLING ME WHAT A GREAT TIME
YOU WERE HAVING,

15:04.945 --> 15:08.198
SO WHATEVER YOU WERE DOING,
WHOEVER --

15:08.198 --> 15:12.032
HE, SHE, THEY, WHATEVER --

15:12.032 --> 15:14.664
IT WASN'T WITH HIM,
AND THAT'S ALL.

15:16.166 --> 15:18.208
I WANT TO BE HERE
FOR YOU,

15:18.208 --> 15:23.423
BUT I LIKE DEREK
AND I HATE LYING.

15:23.423 --> 15:25.095
Curt: [ COUGHING ]

15:25.095 --> 15:27.387
OH G-- GREY! PIERCE!
GET IN HERE!

15:27.387 --> 15:30.050
OKAY, OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

15:30.050 --> 15:32.812
Meredith: CALL THE O.R.
LET THEM KNOW WE'RE COMING NOW!
OH, GOD, CURT!

15:34.144 --> 15:36.516
ROBBINS.
LET'S GO SCRUB.
COMING.

15:36.516 --> 15:38.818
LISTEN, JUST TALK TO HER,
AND -- AND MAYBE BUY HER A ROBE.

15:38.818 --> 15:40.360
[ SCOFFS ]
WHY WOULD I DO THAT?

15:40.360 --> 15:42.272
WAS THIS ABOUT
THE NAKED RESIDENT?

15:42.272 --> 15:43.943
OOH, YOU AND WILSON,
YOU'RE A THING.

15:43.943 --> 15:44.985
YOU KNOW WHAT?
LET'S NOT.

15:44.985 --> 15:47.067
AND ROBBINS CAN GET HANDSY
WITH THE RESIDENTS.

15:47.067 --> 15:48.068
REALLY?

15:48.068 --> 15:49.069
I DO NOT!

15:49.069 --> 15:50.700
LAST YEAR,
SHE GOT HANDSY.

15:50.700 --> 15:53.203
H.R. GOT INVOLVED.
THERE ARE POLICIES NOW.

15:53.203 --> 15:54.874
OH!
BECAUSE OF YOU?

15:54.874 --> 15:56.876
ROBBINS,
THAT'S INCREDIBLE.

15:56.876 --> 15:59.789
IT'S NOT.
IT -- BOTH OF YOU STOP, OKAY?

15:59.789 --> 16:01.001
ALEX,
IT'S INAPPROPRIATE.

16:01.001 --> 16:02.752
SHE'S A RESIDENT.
I'M HER SUPERIOR.

16:02.752 --> 16:04.174
I'M A GIRL
WHO LIKES GIRLS.

16:04.174 --> 16:05.175
IT JUST PUTS US BOTH
IN A VERY AWKWARD POSITION,

16:05.175 --> 16:06.256
AND YOU SHOULD
RESPECT THAT.

16:06.256 --> 16:07.717
WELL, I'M KIND OF DOWN
FOR WHATEVER HAPPENS.

16:07.717 --> 16:08.848
[ SCOFFS ]
I'M GONNA KILL YOU.

16:08.848 --> 16:10.430
HEY.
HEY.

16:10.430 --> 16:12.182
YOU NEED TO START PUTTING ON
PANTS AROUND THE HOUSE

16:12.182 --> 16:14.144
'CAUSE ROBBINS
KEEPS CHECKING OUT YOUR ASS.

16:14.144 --> 16:16.186
NO. NO.
ALEX, NO.

16:16.186 --> 16:17.097
YOU DON'T NEED TO
PUT PANTS ON, OKAY?

16:17.097 --> 16:18.898
YOUR ASS IS --
IT -- FINE.

16:18.898 --> 16:20.270
SEE?
THAT'S REPORTABLE.

16:20.270 --> 16:22.062
NO! I...
[ SCOFFS ]

16:22.062 --> 16:23.563
I HATE YOU ALL.

16:23.563 --> 16:25.065
I HAVE SURGERY.

16:25.065 --> 16:26.566
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

16:26.566 --> 16:27.907
THIS IS THE BEST DAY.

16:27.907 --> 16:29.069
[ LAUGHS ]

16:29.069 --> 16:32.112
OH, GOD, I'M AWFUL.

16:32.112 --> 16:34.574
THERE IS NOTHING WRONG
WITH TODD.

16:34.574 --> 16:37.077
HE'S -- HE'S NICE
AND HE'S STABLE

16:37.077 --> 16:41.121
AND HE CARES FOR ME
DEEPLY...

16:41.121 --> 16:42.882
SO DEEPLY.

16:42.882 --> 16:44.834
AND HE'S CLINGY,
AND HE LOVES TO --

16:44.834 --> 16:46.426
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT TO CALL IT,

16:46.426 --> 16:48.338
BUT HE LIKES TO...
PET ME.

16:48.338 --> 16:49.889
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S REALLY SOFT,

16:49.889 --> 16:51.761
AND IT -- UGH!

16:51.761 --> 16:53.843
HE'S BORING.

16:53.843 --> 16:55.055
SO, I JUST STARTED
DOING THIS THING

16:55.055 --> 16:58.348
WHERE I PRETEND TO FAINT
SO HE'LL STOP TALKING.

16:58.348 --> 17:01.771
WOW, THAT IS...

17:03.063 --> 17:04.404
DIABOLICAL.

17:04.404 --> 17:06.106
WHY DON'T YOU JUST TELL HIM
THE TRUTH?

17:06.106 --> 17:07.527
BECAUSE
IT WOULD KILL HIM.

17:07.527 --> 17:10.490
I MEAN, HE WANTS TO TAKE THINGS
TO THE NEXT LEVEL,

17:10.490 --> 17:13.613
BUT THE MORE THAT HE FEELS,
THE LESS I DO.

17:13.613 --> 17:16.286
AND THEN TODAY,
WE WERE IN THE PARK,

17:16.286 --> 17:17.957
AND HE GOT DOWN
ON ONE KNEE

17:17.957 --> 17:20.080
AND HE LOOKED UP AT ME
WITH HIS BIG WET EYES,

17:20.080 --> 17:22.212
SO I JUST --
FAKED IT.

17:22.212 --> 17:25.044
I DIDN'T REALIZE HOW CLOSE I WAS
TO THE STEPS.

17:25.044 --> 17:28.628
BUT I HAD TO GO WITH IT
ALL THE WAY DOWN.

17:29.799 --> 17:31.010
YOU CAN REALLY COMMIT.

17:31.010 --> 17:33.553
YEAH.

17:33.553 --> 17:34.634
BUT NOT TO TODD.

17:37.387 --> 17:39.679
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
SHEPHERD, HOW'S HERMAN?

17:39.679 --> 17:41.231
ANY CHANGES
TO THE TUMOR?

17:41.231 --> 17:43.103
OH, IT'S GROWN A LITTLE
INFERIORLY.

17:43.103 --> 17:45.024
UH, BUT IT'S STILL WITHIN
THE MARGINS I EXPECTED.

17:45.024 --> 17:47.357
WHY?
I WAS JUST CHECKING.

17:47.357 --> 17:49.739
ACTUALLY, UM...

17:49.739 --> 17:53.113
HER BEHAVIOR IS --

17:53.113 --> 17:54.324
SHE'S STEALING FURNITURE.

17:54.324 --> 17:55.285
OH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:55.285 --> 17:58.118
AND...SHE WAS FLIRTING
WITH ME.

17:59.329 --> 18:00.410
HERMAN FLIRTED WITH YOU?

18:00.410 --> 18:02.081
I THINK SO.

18:02.081 --> 18:04.083
I...YEAH.

18:04.083 --> 18:05.255
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:05.255 --> 18:06.916
DID YOU
TAKE HER UP ON IT?

18:06.916 --> 18:09.048
I MEAN,
SHE'S VERY ATTRACTIVE.

18:09.048 --> 18:11.050
NO. UH, YES, SHE --
SHE IS, BU--

18:11.050 --> 18:12.472
AND TALL.

18:12.472 --> 18:15.715
I MEAN, SHE MIGHT BE THE TALLEST
PERSON IN THE HOSPITAL.

18:15.715 --> 18:17.477
YOU MIGHT FIND TALL PEOPLE
ATTRACTIVE.

18:17.477 --> 18:18.928
I DON'T KNOW.
NO, I DON'T.

18:18.928 --> 18:21.020
NOT AS A RULE,

18:21.020 --> 18:22.982
BUT PROFESSIONALLY,
IT'S NOT A GOOD IDEA.

18:22.982 --> 18:24.724
IS THAT A RULE?

18:24.724 --> 18:25.685
NO CO-WORKERS?

18:25.685 --> 18:27.066
DIDN'T SAY THAT.

18:27.066 --> 18:28.188
I-I LIKE CO-WORKERS.

18:28.188 --> 18:30.940
I-I -- BUT THE --
THE HOSPITAL, WE HAVE RULES

18:30.940 --> 18:31.941
THAT ARE, UM...

18:33.363 --> 18:34.784
THANK YOU FOR THE UPDATE.

18:34.784 --> 18:37.157
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

18:39.699 --> 18:41.201
YOU WANTED A CONSULT?

18:41.201 --> 18:42.001
NOT ME.

18:42.001 --> 18:43.203
ME.

18:43.203 --> 18:45.915
MOM.

18:45.915 --> 18:47.417
I ASKED YOU TO GO.

18:47.417 --> 18:50.630
I NEED YOU TO TAKE A LOOK
AT THIS INCISION, SWEETHEART.

18:51.921 --> 18:54.053
SHE'S NOT JUST TRYING
TO CHECK ON ME AND APRIL?

18:54.053 --> 18:56.516
DON'T LOOK AT ME.
I GOT PLAYED, TOO.

19:00.560 --> 19:01.641
THEY JUST TOOK HIM IN.

19:01.641 --> 19:03.022
HOW THE HELL
DID THIS HAPPEN?

19:03.022 --> 19:05.185
HE WAS SITTING UP
AND TALKING TO ME AN HOUR AGO.

19:05.185 --> 19:06.976
WELL, WE KNEW
ABOUT THE SPLEEN.

19:06.976 --> 19:08.648
IT MADE
HIS STOMACH MUSCLES BLEED,

19:08.648 --> 19:10.480
BUT PIERCE WILL CLIP THEM
AND GREY --

19:10.480 --> 19:12.402
YOU WERE RIGHT.
YOU WERE RIGHT ABOUT THE DRUGS.

19:12.402 --> 19:15.154
I-I DIDN'T WANT TO BELIEVE IT
AT FIRST, BUT IT'S OBVIOUS.

19:15.154 --> 19:16.236
HE -- HE'S USING.

19:16.236 --> 19:17.907
OKAY, NOW,
WE SHOULDN'T JUMP --

19:17.907 --> 19:19.038
I'LL GET HIM IN REHAB.

19:19.038 --> 19:21.120
AS SOON AS HE CAN WALK
OUT OF HERE, I'M GO--

19:21.120 --> 19:22.912
BEN, WAIT.

19:22.912 --> 19:25.955
WHAT DO YOU THINK IT IS?
COKE? CRYSTAL?

19:25.955 --> 19:28.548
COME ON, Y-YOU'RE USUALLY RIGHT
ABOUT THESE THINGS.

19:28.548 --> 19:30.500
TELL ME.

19:30.500 --> 19:32.212
I THINK...

19:32.212 --> 19:34.053
YOU SHOULD
TALK TO CURT.

19:36.756 --> 19:38.798
IS THERE -- THERE SOMETHING
YOU'RE NOT TELLING ME?

19:38.798 --> 19:41.301
AFTER SURGERY,
HE'LL TELL YOU EVERYTHING.

19:41.301 --> 19:43.473
TELL ME WHAT?
MIRANDA.

19:43.473 --> 19:45.064
JUST TALK TO HIM.
HE'LL --

19:45.064 --> 19:46.686
BUT WHAT IF I DON'T GET
THE CHANCE TO?

19:46.686 --> 19:48.438
WHAT -- WHAT IF HE DOESN'T
COME OUT OF SURGERY?

19:48.438 --> 19:50.189
OH, THAT'S NONSENSE.
NOW, JUST CALM DOWN.

19:50.189 --> 19:51.190
CALM DOWN?

19:51.190 --> 19:52.732
I'M BEING LIED TO
BY MY BROTHER,

19:52.732 --> 19:54.193
AND NOW I'M BEING LIED TO
BY MY WIFE.

19:54.193 --> 19:55.405
I'M NOT LYING TO YOU.

19:55.405 --> 19:56.986
WELL, NO ONE'S TELLING ME
THE DAMN TRUTH!

19:56.986 --> 19:58.818
[ GRUNTS ] I'LL TELL YOU!

19:58.818 --> 19:59.949
[ HUFFS ]

19:59.949 --> 20:01.821
IT'S ONLY BECAUSE
WHEN HE TELLS YOU,

20:01.821 --> 20:03.953
YOU NEED TO REACT BETTER
THAN THIS, BEN WARREN.

20:03.953 --> 20:04.994
WHAT IS IT?

20:04.994 --> 20:07.667
OKAY, CURT IS...

20:07.667 --> 20:08.878
[ SIGHS ]

20:08.878 --> 20:10.920
CURT IS TRANSITIONING.

20:10.920 --> 20:12.422
HE...

20:12.422 --> 20:15.134
SHE IS TRANSGENDER.

20:15.134 --> 20:18.678
AND SHE IDENTIFIES
AS FEMALE,

20:18.678 --> 20:22.762
AND SHE WANTS TO LIVE LIFE
AS A WOMAN.

20:22.762 --> 20:26.436
YOUR BROTHER
IS BECOMING YOUR SISTER.

20:30.730 --> 20:33.112
[ LAUGHS ]

20:33.112 --> 20:34.484
OH, MY GOD.

20:34.484 --> 20:37.156
OH --
OH, THAT SON OF A BITCH.

20:37.156 --> 20:38.528
HE --
HE PUT YOU UP TO THIS.

20:38.528 --> 20:39.989
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:55.675 --> 20:57.256
Maggie:
BLEEDING IS CONTROLLED.

20:57.256 --> 21:00.550
CLAMPING THE HILUM.
SUTURE LIGATURE.

21:00.550 --> 21:02.181
SO, WHAT DID YOU SAY
WHEN HE CALLED?

21:02.181 --> 21:05.475
THE FIRST TIME, I SAID
THAT YOU WERE IN THE SHOWER.

21:07.307 --> 21:10.520
LIGATING
THE GASTRIC VESSELS.

21:10.520 --> 21:13.813
THE SECOND TIME,
I SAID YOU WERE TAKING A NAP.

21:13.813 --> 21:15.194
AND THE THIRD TIME,

21:15.194 --> 21:19.359
I SAID HUNT CALLED YOU IN
FOR AN EMERGENT RECTAL ABSCESS.

21:19.359 --> 21:21.030
I HATE LYING.

21:21.030 --> 21:22.992
I DIDN'T WANT TO
SPOIL ANYTHING.

21:28.328 --> 21:30.540
I NEED TO DISSECT
THE SPLENORENAL LIGAMENT.

21:30.540 --> 21:31.541
METZ.

21:40.219 --> 21:41.381
HEY, OKAY.

21:41.381 --> 21:43.803
PIERCE JUST CONTROLLED
THE GASTRIC BLEEDS WITH CLIPS,

21:43.803 --> 21:46.225
AND NOW GREY IS FINISHING
TAKING OUT THE SPLEEN.

21:46.225 --> 21:49.228
ALL RIGHT, NOW, UM --
HE'S UPSET ABOUT DAD.

21:49.228 --> 21:51.771
HE'S OBVIOUSLY HAVING SOME SORT
OF EMOTIONAL BREAKDOWN,

21:51.771 --> 21:52.982
SO WE'LL GET HIM
A PSYCH CONSULT.

21:52.982 --> 21:54.354
NO, WE WON'T.

21:54.354 --> 21:57.026
CURT'S CRAZY.
THIS MAKES NO SENSE.

21:57.026 --> 21:59.359
ALL RIGHT, THE ONLY THING
THAT DOES MAKE SENSE RIGHT NOW

21:59.359 --> 22:02.111
IS THAT AFTER THE SURGERY,
YOU WILL TALK TO CURT...

22:02.111 --> 22:06.115
YEAH.
...AND YOU WILL LISTEN TO CURT
TELL YOU HER GOOD NEWS,

22:06.115 --> 22:08.037
AND IT IS GOOD NEWS.

22:08.037 --> 22:09.449
AND YOU WILL LISTEN,

22:09.449 --> 22:12.372
AND YOU WILL TELL HER
THAT YOU LOVE HER

22:12.372 --> 22:15.254
AND TELL HER THAT
YOU'LL ALWAYS BE HERE FOR HER.

22:16.836 --> 22:18.548
OKAY, SO AFTER
THE FETOSCOPE IS INSERTED,

22:18.548 --> 22:20.009
THEN I WILL DEPLOY
THE SHUNT,

22:20.009 --> 22:21.671
AND YOU'LL MANIPULATE
THE CAMERA, RIGHT?

22:21.671 --> 22:22.802
YOU'RE A HYPOCRITE.

22:22.802 --> 22:24.013
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

22:24.013 --> 22:27.096
YOU, UH, WERE SO HIGH AND MIGHTY
WHEN I WAS BOFFING GRAHAM.

22:27.096 --> 22:30.019
WHICH ONE WAS IT?
WHICH RESIDENT DID YOU SULLY?

22:30.019 --> 22:31.771
OH, GOD.
I KNEW THAT YOU WOULD...

22:31.771 --> 22:33.022
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:33.022 --> 22:35.024
YOU CAN'T SUDDENLY BECOME
INTERESTING AND THEN CLAM UP.

22:35.024 --> 22:38.357
IT -- IT WAS A YEAR AGO,
AND SHE'S GONE NOW.

22:39.318 --> 22:40.980
WEREN'T YOU MARRIED
LAST YEAR?
YES.

22:40.980 --> 22:42.862
NO. WELL,
WE -- WE WERE BROKEN UP.

22:42.862 --> 22:44.113
I THOUGHT YOU JUST SPLIT.

22:44.113 --> 22:45.655
THIS WAS A DIFFERENT TI--
[SIGHS]

22:45.655 --> 22:47.487
I CHEATED ON CALLIE, OKAY?

22:47.487 --> 22:48.698
OH, MY GOD.

22:48.698 --> 22:50.119
HOW HAVE YOU BEEN
HIDING THIS FROM ME?

22:50.119 --> 22:51.040
HIDING WHAT?

22:51.040 --> 22:53.252
THE DIRT.
YOU'RE DIRTY.

22:53.252 --> 22:54.954
[ SCOFFS ]

22:54.954 --> 22:56.456
AND HERE I THOUGHT
YOU WERE NO FUN AT ALL.

22:56.456 --> 22:57.547
OH, STOP IT.
I'M --

22:57.547 --> 22:59.549
YOU'RE A DIRTY,
DIRTY GIRL.

22:59.549 --> 23:00.760
[ LAUGHS ]

23:00.760 --> 23:02.131
YOU'RE DIRTY.

23:07.136 --> 23:10.099
MINIMAL SWELLING.
I LIKE THAT.

23:10.099 --> 23:11.811
HEY, CAN I GET AN E.T.A
ON WHEN YOU'RE CLOSING

23:11.811 --> 23:13.773
JUST SO I CAN PREP
THE LEG?
ONE LAST VESSEL HERE.

23:13.773 --> 23:17.106
SO, SHE THREW HERSELF
DOWN A FLIGHT OF STAIRS

23:17.106 --> 23:19.779
JUST TO AVOID TELLING HIM
YES OR NO?

23:19.779 --> 23:20.780
MM-HMM.

23:20.780 --> 23:22.361
HAVE YOU MET
THE BOYFRIEND?

23:22.361 --> 23:25.695
WILSON, GO LET HIM KNOW THAT HER
BRAIN SURGERY WAS SUCCESSFUL.

23:25.695 --> 23:27.116
BRING TISSUES.

23:27.116 --> 23:28.528
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:28.528 --> 23:30.790
OH.
POOR GUY.

23:30.790 --> 23:31.871
POOR GUY?

23:31.871 --> 23:33.993
I'M SEWING HER BRAIN SHUT
RIGHT NOW.

23:33.993 --> 23:35.034
OH,
TODD'S THE PROBLEM HERE?

23:35.034 --> 23:36.456
WHY?
'CAUSE HE CARES TOO MUCH?

23:36.456 --> 23:38.207
HE FEELS TOO MUCH?

23:38.207 --> 23:39.629
HE'S -- HE'S WILLING
TO DEVOTE HIMSELF FULLY

23:39.629 --> 23:42.001
TO ANOTHER PERSON.
THAT'S THE PROBLEM?

23:42.001 --> 23:45.254
IF IT MAKES THE OTHER PERSON
WANT TO PASS OUT, YEAH.

23:46.385 --> 23:47.927
WELL, THEN THAT'S IT.

23:47.927 --> 23:49.929
THAT'S WHY I CAN'T
PICK PEOPLE UP ANYMORE,

23:49.929 --> 23:51.971
BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO PUT THEM BACK DOWN.

23:51.971 --> 23:53.182
THAT'S WHY I HAVE NO GAME.

23:53.182 --> 23:55.605
I USED TO HAVE GAME.

23:55.605 --> 23:57.687
I HAD SUCH GAME.

23:57.687 --> 23:59.148
YEAH?

23:59.148 --> 24:03.112
I USED TO BE FUN AND COOL
AND SEXY AND GO TO BARS

24:03.112 --> 24:05.064
AND DO THIS THING
WHERE YOU MAKE EYE CONTACT ONCE

24:05.064 --> 24:06.656
AND LOOK AWAY.

24:06.656 --> 24:09.739
JUST REEL THEM IN
WITHOUT A WORD.

24:09.739 --> 24:11.370
SUCH GAME.

24:11.370 --> 24:14.033
HEY,
WHAT WAS YOUR SECRET?

24:15.124 --> 24:16.125
DRUGS.

24:16.125 --> 24:17.917
I WAS ON DRUGS.
MM.

24:17.917 --> 24:18.958
SO, I'M LEAVING OUT

24:18.958 --> 24:20.169
THE TERRIBLE,
TERRIBLE REPERCUSSIONS,

24:20.169 --> 24:22.882
BUT EVER SINCE I GOT OFF
THE DRUGS, I'VE GOTTEN WORSE.

24:22.882 --> 24:25.384
NOW I'M JUST ALL MUMBLING
AND VOMITING WORDS

24:25.384 --> 24:29.088
AND NO COOL, NO SEXY,
NO GAME AT ALL.

24:29.088 --> 24:31.390
SAME HERE.
GAME OVER.

24:31.390 --> 24:34.183
I WANT TO BE CLEAR --
I AM IN NO WAY

24:34.183 --> 24:36.726
ENDORSING NARCOTICS
AS A DATING AID.

24:36.726 --> 24:38.097
UNDERSTOOD.

24:38.097 --> 24:40.229
SO, DINNER'S COMING?

24:40.229 --> 24:41.270
YES, MOM.

24:41.270 --> 24:43.232
YOU STILL HAVEN'T TOLD ME.
HOW'S APRIL?

24:43.232 --> 24:45.605
MOM, SHE'S ALL RIGHT.

24:45.605 --> 24:47.567
AND I'M FINE.

24:47.567 --> 24:48.608
WE'RE DOING OKAY.

24:48.608 --> 24:50.029
MM-HMM.

24:50.029 --> 24:51.410
I DON'T BELIEVE THAT
FOR ONE SECOND.

24:51.410 --> 24:52.702
[ SIGHS ] MOM,
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO SAY?

24:52.702 --> 24:54.994
MOM, SHE'S SAD,
OBVIOUSLY.

24:54.994 --> 24:56.826
APRIL IS ANGRY, OKAY?

24:56.826 --> 24:59.118
ABOUT THE BABY,
ABOUT GOD.

24:59.118 --> 25:01.000
SHE JUST NEEDS HER SPACE.

25:01.000 --> 25:02.501
AND I CAN'T HELP HER.

25:02.501 --> 25:04.043
I JUST MAKE HER CRAZY,

25:04.043 --> 25:06.756
WHICH JUST MAKES ME
FEEL USELESS.

25:06.756 --> 25:09.218
SHE DOESN'T NEED SPACE SO MUCH
AS THE ILLUSION OF SPACE.

25:10.630 --> 25:12.261
YOU SHOULD DO WHAT I DO.

25:12.261 --> 25:15.094
STAY OUT OF HER WAY,
BUT NOT TOO FAR.

25:15.094 --> 25:16.596
FIND SOMETHING ELSE
TO OCCUPY YOUR MIND.

25:16.596 --> 25:18.808
WORK IS GOOD.

25:18.808 --> 25:22.902
NOW, BE CLOSE,
BUT JUST OUT OF SIGHT.

25:22.902 --> 25:25.524
AND YOU'LL BE THERE FOR HER
WHEN SHE'S READY.

25:27.106 --> 25:31.110
OKAY, I'M PRETTY SURE WHAT
YOU JUST DESCRIBED IS STALKING.

25:31.110 --> 25:33.613
YOUR ABDOMINAL CLOSURE
SHOULD BE FINE.

25:36.455 --> 25:38.457
IS THAT WHAT THIS WEEKEND
WAS FOR YOU?

25:38.457 --> 25:41.080
SOMETHING ELSE
TO OCCUPY YOUR MIND?

25:44.874 --> 25:46.545
I'M NOT CHEATING
ON MY HUSBAND.

25:46.545 --> 25:47.927
THEN WHERE WERE YOU?

25:47.927 --> 25:49.719
IT'S REALLY
NOT THAT BIG A DEAL.

25:49.719 --> 25:51.971
THEN WHY ARE YOU BEING
SO WEIRD ABOUT IT?

25:51.971 --> 25:53.763
YOU HAVE TO TELL ME
SOMETHING.

25:53.763 --> 25:54.764
I HAVE TO?

25:54.764 --> 25:55.765
I LIED FOR YOU.

25:55.765 --> 25:57.767
I'M SORRY IF I PUT YOU
IN A POSITION

25:57.767 --> 26:00.059
WHERE YOU FELT LIKE
YOU HAD TO LIE FOR ME,

26:00.059 --> 26:02.141
BUT THAT DOESN'T MAKE THIS
ANY OF YOUR BUSINESS.

26:02.141 --> 26:03.232
OKAY, MAYBE NOT.

26:03.232 --> 26:06.145
I JUST [SIGHS]

26:06.145 --> 26:08.948
I THOUGHT WE WERE
FINALLY GETTING SOMEWHERE.

26:08.948 --> 26:11.070
YOU TRUSTED ME
WITH YOUR KIDS.

26:11.070 --> 26:12.531
I TRUST MY BABYSITTER
WITH MY KIDS.

26:12.531 --> 26:14.323
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
I OWE HER MY LIFE STORY.

26:16.616 --> 26:18.868
PIERCE, I'M SORRY.

26:18.868 --> 26:20.750
NO. NO, IT'S FINE.
IT'S FINE.
THAT CAME OUT WRONG.

26:20.750 --> 26:21.751
YOU'RE RIGHT.

26:21.751 --> 26:22.752
JUST DO ME A FAVOR.

26:22.752 --> 26:24.333
NEXT TIME,
CALL YOUR BABYSITTER.

26:24.333 --> 26:26.505
LEAVE ME OUT OF IT.

26:33.052 --> 26:35.174
OH, THERE SHE IS.
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

26:35.174 --> 26:37.096
HOW IS SHE?
IS SHE ALL WELL AGAIN?

26:37.096 --> 26:40.059
SHE'S GONNA BE FINE.
BOTH SURGERIES WENT VERY WELL.

26:40.059 --> 26:41.180
THANK YOU. THANK --

26:41.180 --> 26:42.271
THANK YOU.
MM-HMM.

26:42.271 --> 26:45.224
HILL.
I'M GONNA TAKE YOU HOME.

26:45.224 --> 26:47.436
I'M GONNA MAKE SURE
THAT YOU HAVE

26:47.436 --> 26:49.528
EVERYTHING YOU NEED,
ALL RIGHT?

26:49.528 --> 26:51.230
You tell him right now.

26:55.364 --> 26:57.036
TODD.

26:57.036 --> 27:00.039
YOU HAVE BEEN SO SWEET,

27:00.039 --> 27:02.121
AND YOU HAVE BEEN
SO KIND,

27:02.121 --> 27:04.664
AND I HAVE BEEN UNFAIR
TO YOU.

27:04.664 --> 27:06.125
NO, NO.
Shh, Shh, Shh, Shh, Shh.

27:06.125 --> 27:07.506
NO,
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

27:07.506 --> 27:08.507
UH...

27:08.507 --> 27:11.550
I LOVE YOU.
I'M RIGHT HERE.

27:11.550 --> 27:14.463
AND I'M NEVER LEAVING YOU.

27:15.634 --> 27:17.096
EVER.

27:18.928 --> 27:20.559
OH, HILLARY.
HILLARY?

27:20.559 --> 27:21.470
HILLARY?!
OH.

27:21.470 --> 27:22.311
SHE FAINTED!

27:22.311 --> 27:24.023
HELP HER!

27:24.023 --> 27:25.685
FOR GOD SAKE.

27:25.685 --> 27:27.817
SHE CAN'T TAKE ANOTHER FALL
LIKE THAT.

27:27.817 --> 27:29.859
TODD, WHAT HILLARY'S
TRYING TO TELL YOU

27:29.859 --> 27:32.361
IS THAT SHE WANTS TO
BREAK UP WITH YOU.

27:32.361 --> 27:34.113
WHAT?
I'M SO SORRY.

27:34.113 --> 27:35.985
I KNOW THAT ALL YOU WANT
IS TO HELP HER,

27:35.985 --> 27:37.366
BUT SHE DOESN'T WANT THAT.

27:37.366 --> 27:39.448
SHE DOESN'T DESERVE IT.
SHE'S FAKING THIS RIGHT NOW.

27:41.450 --> 27:43.042
WHAT?
TODD.

27:43.042 --> 27:47.626
YOU DESERVE SOMEONE
WHO WANTS YOU THERE, YOU KNOW?

27:47.626 --> 27:50.549
UM, SOMEONE WHO NEEDS
THE KIND OF ATTENTION

27:50.549 --> 27:52.051
THAT ONLY YOU CAN GIVE,

27:52.051 --> 27:55.214
AND IT'S NOT GONNA BE HILLARY,
OKAY, AND IT SHOULDN'T BE.

27:55.214 --> 27:56.295
[ GROANS ]

27:56.295 --> 27:58.257
AND YOU WILL BE FINE...
WITHOUT HER,

27:58.257 --> 28:01.220
AND IT MAY TAKE A WHILE
TO FIND THE RIGHT PERSON,

28:01.220 --> 28:02.641
BUT YOU WILL FIND HER.

28:02.641 --> 28:04.183
YOU SHOULD START LOOKING,
OKAY?

28:04.183 --> 28:05.514
SHE'S RIGHT.

28:05.514 --> 28:07.977
DON'T WASTE ANOTHER MINUTE.
START RIGHT NOW.

28:17.026 --> 28:18.447
[ SIGHS ]

28:18.447 --> 28:19.819
THERE.

28:19.819 --> 28:21.200
THANK YOU.

28:24.163 --> 28:27.787
JUST -- JUST TELL ME,
WHERE'S THIS ALL COMING FROM?

28:28.998 --> 28:32.041
IT'S COMING FROM ME.
THIS IS WHO I AM.

28:32.041 --> 28:33.632
SINCE WHEN?

28:33.632 --> 28:35.714
I MEAN, WHAT,
YOU JUST SUDDENLY DECIDED --

28:35.714 --> 28:39.138
BENJI,
I'VE KNOWN SINCE I WAS 5.

28:39.138 --> 28:41.140
5?
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:41.140 --> 28:43.763
BECAUSE, YOU KNOW, I WANTED TO
PLAY FOR THE BEARS WHEN I WAS 5

28:43.763 --> 28:46.936
BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW CRAP
WHEN YOU'RE 5.

28:46.936 --> 28:48.607
I KNEW THIS.

28:48.607 --> 28:50.689
YEAH,
BUT WHY DIDN'T I KNOW IT?

28:50.689 --> 28:52.731
WE SHARED A ROOM
FOR 18 YEARS.

28:54.313 --> 28:56.776
YOU EVER HAVE THAT DREAM
WHERE YOU'RE PUSHED OUT ON STAGE

28:56.776 --> 28:59.028
AND EVERYBODY KNOWS THEIR LINES
EXCEPT YOU?

29:00.279 --> 29:02.031
AND YOU'RE IN SOME COSTUME

29:02.031 --> 29:04.703
OR YOU'RE NAKED OR --
OR WHATEVER.

29:04.703 --> 29:07.166
AND YOU'RE JUST
TRAPPED THERE.

29:07.166 --> 29:08.167
YOU CAN'T...

29:09.959 --> 29:11.710
THAT WAS MY WHOLE LIFE.

29:11.710 --> 29:14.133
EVERY DAY OF MY LIFE,
PRETENDING.

29:17.256 --> 29:19.758
BENJI,
I'M TIRED OF PRETENDING.

29:21.090 --> 29:25.054
I JUST WANT TO BE HAPPY
WITH WHO I AM.

29:27.726 --> 29:29.939
CAN YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

29:29.939 --> 29:33.813
SO, NOW YOU GIVE A DAMN
ABOUT WHAT I THINK?

29:33.813 --> 29:35.815
NOW SUDDENLY IT MATTERS
THAT I UNDERSTAND?

29:35.815 --> 29:37.817
YOU KNOW IT DOES.

29:37.817 --> 29:40.029
I'M -- I'M JUST SUPPOSED TO
BE OKAY WITH THIS?

29:40.029 --> 29:43.322
I-I'M JUST SUPPOSED TO
ACCEPT THIS?

29:50.119 --> 29:51.670
WA--WAI--

29:51.670 --> 29:53.332
OKAY, I'LL GO TALK TO HIM.

29:53.332 --> 29:55.584
DON'T BOTHER.

29:57.126 --> 29:59.798
HOW SOON DO YOU THINK
I CAN GET OUT OF HERE?

30:05.304 --> 30:07.636
I DON'T IMAGINE
YOU NEED A RIDE TO THE AIRPORT.

30:07.636 --> 30:10.980
I HAVE A CAR.

30:10.980 --> 30:12.601
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

30:12.601 --> 30:14.733
YOU SCRUB IN WITH ME,
YOU TAKE OVER THE O.R.

30:14.733 --> 30:16.896
SO YOU CAN CALL YOUR SON
ON A PHONY CONSULT?

30:16.896 --> 30:18.527
I NEEDED TO KNOW
HOW HE WAS DOING.

30:18.527 --> 30:19.989
I'M TALKING ABOUT US.

30:19.989 --> 30:21.861
WHAT ABOUT US, RICHARD?

30:21.861 --> 30:23.202
IT LOOKS LIKE
YOU GOT WHAT YOU WANTED

30:23.202 --> 30:24.153
AND YOU'RE RUNNING
OUT THE DOOR.

30:24.153 --> 30:25.494
YOU USED ME.

30:25.494 --> 30:28.117
I SEEM TO RECALL YOUR SAYING
I USE PEOPLE ALL THE TIME --

30:28.117 --> 30:30.039
CRISTINA YANG,
THE HARPER AVERY.

30:30.039 --> 30:31.660
SO, WHY ARE YOU
SO SURPRISED NOW?

30:31.660 --> 30:33.452
I WAS ANGRY
WHEN I SAID THOSE THINGS.

30:33.452 --> 30:35.834
AND I WAS ANGRY
WHEN I HEARD THEM.

30:35.834 --> 30:37.917
[ SIGHS ]

30:39.879 --> 30:43.012
I THOUGHT
AFTER THE LAST FEW DAYS, I...

30:43.012 --> 30:45.054
I THOUGHT
WE'D MOVED ON FROM THAT.

30:45.054 --> 30:50.229
RICHARD, YOU WERE HERE FOR ME
IN A TERRIBLE TIME.

30:50.229 --> 30:53.973
I APPRECIATE THAT,
BUT I'M STILL ME,

30:53.973 --> 30:56.185
AND YOU'RE NOT OKAY
WITH WHO I AM.

30:56.185 --> 30:58.687
ONE MINUTE, YOU FIND
A POWERFUL WOMAN ATTRACTIVE,

30:58.687 --> 31:00.779
THE NEXT MINUTE,
YOUR FEELINGS ARE HURT.

31:00.779 --> 31:02.191
YOU CAN'T HAVE IT
BOTH WAYS.

31:02.191 --> 31:04.033
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
FIGURE THAT OUT

31:04.033 --> 31:06.695
BEFORE WE MOVE ON
ANYWHERE.

31:19.418 --> 31:22.381
I WENT TO THE AIRPORT,
I GOT THROUGH SECURITY,

31:22.381 --> 31:23.672
I WENT UP TO THE GATE,

31:23.672 --> 31:26.715
THEY CALLED MY BOARDING GROUP,
AND I JUST STOOD THERE.

31:26.715 --> 31:30.719
♪ TO SEEING SHOWS IN EVENING
CLOTHES WITH YOU ♪
I FROZE.
I DIDN'T GET ON THE PLANE.

31:30.719 --> 31:33.062
I WATCHED THE PLANE TAKE OFF
FROM BEHIND THE GLASS...

31:33.062 --> 31:35.394
♪ FROM NERVOUS TOUCH
TO GETTING DRUNK ♪
...I GOT IN MY CAR,
AND I LEFT.

31:35.394 --> 31:38.017
OH, MEREDITH.

31:38.017 --> 31:40.279
I DIDN'T KNOW
HOW TO TELL ANYONE...

31:40.279 --> 31:45.154
♪ TO STAYING UP
AND WAKING UP WITH YOU ♪
...THAT I DIDN'T GET ON THE
PLANE TO VISIT MY HUSBAND.

31:45.154 --> 31:47.526
♪ BUT NOW WE'RE SLEEPING
AT THE EDGE ♪
SO, I DROVE TO ONE
OF THOSE HOTELS BY THE AIRPORT.

31:47.526 --> 31:51.240
♪ HOLDING SOMETHING
WE DON'T NEED ♪
AND YOU STAYED THERE
BY YOURSELF ALL WEEKEND?

31:51.240 --> 31:52.411
YEAH.

31:52.411 --> 31:54.373
♪ ALL THIS DELUSION
IN OUR HEADS ♪

31:54.373 --> 31:55.995
♪ IS GONNA BRING US
TO OUR KNEES ♪
YOU WERE EMBARRASSED,
SO YOU HID.

31:55.995 --> 31:57.536
I...I KIND OF GET THAT.

31:57.536 --> 31:58.998
♪ SO COME ON, LET IT GO ♪

31:58.998 --> 32:00.839
WELL, IT'S --
NO, NO, IT'S OKAY.

32:00.839 --> 32:04.003
♪ JUST LET IT BE ♪
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SAY
ANOTHER WORD.

32:04.003 --> 32:06.215
♪ WHY DON'T YOU BE YOU? ♪
THAT MUST'VE BEEN AWFUL.

32:06.215 --> 32:08.177
THOSE CHEAP HOTEL ROOMS
ARE HORRIBLE.

32:08.177 --> 32:11.550
♪ AND I'LL BE ME ♪
YOU MUST'VE FELT TERRIBLE
AND LONELY AND EMBARRASSED...

32:11.550 --> 32:14.893
♪ EVERYTHING'S THAT'S BROKE ♪
...AND I JUST MADE IT WORSE
BY BUGGING YOU...

32:14.893 --> 32:17.016
♪ LEAVE IT TO THE BREEZE ♪
...AND ASKING YOU QUESTIONS
WHEN I SHOULD'VE JUST...

32:17.016 --> 32:21.860
♪ WHY DON'T YOU BE YOU? ♪
I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU DIDN'T TELL ME.

32:21.860 --> 32:22.982
♪ AND I'LL BE ME ♪
IF THAT HAPPENED TO ME,

32:22.982 --> 32:24.363
I WOULDN'T HAVE TOLD ANYBODY,
EITHER.

32:24.363 --> 32:25.364
♪ AND I'LL BE ME ♪
I'M SORRY.

32:25.364 --> 32:26.865
I'M SO SORRY,

32:26.865 --> 32:30.069
BUT THANK YOU...
FOR TELLING ME.

32:30.069 --> 32:32.121
THANK YOU
FOR UNDERSTANDING.

32:37.956 --> 32:41.500
♪ FROM THROWING CLOTHES
ACROSS THE FLOOR ♪

32:42.671 --> 32:45.884
♪ TO TEETH AND CLAWS ♪
BENJAMIN WARREN,
I'M SO DISAPPOINTED IN YOU.

32:45.884 --> 32:47.046
♪ AND SLAMMING DOORS AT YOU ♪
SHE'S YOUR FAMILY.

32:47.046 --> 32:48.347
I GET IT, OKAY?

32:48.347 --> 32:51.350
YOU'RE SO EVOLVED,
SO TOLERANT AND QUICK TO ADJUST.

32:51.350 --> 32:53.802
♪ IF THIS IS ALL
WE'RE LIVING FOR ♪
AND I'M JUST
A -- A DUMB CAVEMAN.

32:53.802 --> 32:54.853
WELL,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE.

32:54.853 --> 32:57.226
♪ WHY ARE WE ♪
25 YEARS, MIRANDA.

32:57.226 --> 32:59.188
♪ DOING IT, DOING IT,
DOING IT ANYMORE ♪
I COUNTED THEM UP TODAY.

32:59.188 --> 33:00.899
THAT'S HOW LONG
WE EITHER SHARED A BEDROOM

33:00.899 --> 33:03.902
OR AN APARTMENT
OR A DAMN TENT IN THE WOODS.

33:03.902 --> 33:06.105
IT'S A LONG TIME FOR THIS
NOT TO COME UP, DON'T YOU THINK?

33:06.105 --> 33:08.067
SHE WASN'T READY.

33:08.067 --> 33:11.160
IF THIS WAS ANYONE ELSE, THERE
WOULDN'T EVEN BE AN ISSUE...

33:11.160 --> 33:14.493
♪ TRYING TO FIT YOUR
HAND INSIDE OF MINE ♪
...BUT I TOLD HIM EVERYTHING.

33:14.493 --> 33:18.207
♪ WHEN WE KNOW
IT JUST DON'T BELONG ♪
I MEAN, FROM MY FIRST CRUSH --
KAHLIA HOGG, FOURTH GRADE --

33:18.207 --> 33:21.920
♪ COULD MAKE ME FEEL RIGHT, NO ♪
TO THE NIGHT I PROPOSED
TO THE GORGEOUS MIRANDA BAILEY.

33:21.920 --> 33:23.502
♪ WHOA ♪
AND EVERYTHING IN BETWEEN.

33:23.502 --> 33:26.175
♪ TRY TO PUSH THIS PROBLEM
UP THE HILL ♪

33:26.175 --> 33:28.006
I HAD TO TELL CURT.

33:28.006 --> 33:30.259
♪ WHEN IT'S JUST TOO HEAVY
TO HOLD ♪
FIRST THING, ALWAYS.

33:30.259 --> 33:33.722
♪ THINK NOW'S THE TIME
TO LET IT SLIDE ♪
BUT NOW HE -- HE'S GOT THE
BIGGEST THING IN HIS LIFE...

33:33.722 --> 33:37.476
♪ SO COME ON, LET IT GO ♪
...AND HE WAITED 25 YEARS
TO TELL ME.

33:37.476 --> 33:39.638
♪ JUST LET IT BE ♪
HOW'S THAT SUPPOSED TO
MAKE ME FEEL?

33:39.638 --> 33:41.980
WELL,
THIS ISN'T ABOUT YOU, BEN.

33:41.980 --> 33:43.142
IT'S HER SONG.

33:43.142 --> 33:45.984
SO GET OFF THE STAGE,
LET HER SING IT.

33:45.984 --> 33:49.068
NO, COULD YOU PLEASE STOP
WITH THAT?

33:49.068 --> 33:50.949
♪ EVERYTHING'S THAT'S BROKE ♪
[ SIGHS ]

33:50.949 --> 33:54.032
♪ LEAVE IT TO THE BREEZE ♪
I FEEL LIKE IT WAS ALL A LIE,
YOU KNOW?

33:54.032 --> 33:57.076
♪ LET THE ASHES FALL ♪

33:57.076 --> 34:00.119
♪ FORGET ABOUT ME ♪
OUR WHOLE LIFE...

34:00.119 --> 34:03.041
♪ COME ON, LET IT GO ♪
HE LIED TO ME.

34:03.041 --> 34:06.545
♪ JUST LET IT BE ♪
WELL,
CURT NEEDS YOUR HELP NOW.

34:06.545 --> 34:08.627
♪ WHY DON'T YOU BE YOU? ♪
YEAH, WELL, IT'S --
IT'S A LITTLE LATE TO ASK.

34:08.627 --> 34:09.668
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:09.668 --> 34:11.970
SHOULD'VE ASKED
25 YEARS AGO.

34:11.970 --> 34:13.972
MNH-MNH.
I'M -- I'M DONE WITH HIM.

34:13.972 --> 34:15.134
♪ AND I'LL BE ME ♪

34:17.306 --> 34:18.307
HER.

34:24.393 --> 34:26.565
[ SIGHS ]

34:33.192 --> 34:34.573
CURT.

34:34.573 --> 34:36.034
UM, THIS IS DR. AVERY.

34:36.034 --> 34:38.157
HE'S A PLASTIC SURGEON.

34:40.459 --> 34:42.911
UM, YOU MIGHT WANT TO
HEAR HIM OUT.

34:42.911 --> 34:45.124
IT'S -- IT'S YOUR CALL.

34:47.166 --> 34:49.338
YOU HAVE A NAME YET?

34:49.338 --> 34:51.470
GUESSING YOU'RE NOT STICKING
WITH CURTIS.

34:54.213 --> 34:56.054
ROSALIND.

34:56.054 --> 34:58.477
THAT'S A BEAUTIFUL NAME.

34:58.477 --> 35:00.179
SO, CAN I CALL YOU
ROSALIND THEN?

35:00.179 --> 35:02.391
'CAUSE I DON'T KNOW
WHAT WE'RE WAITING FOR.

35:05.984 --> 35:08.897
HEY, I'M JACKSON.

35:11.190 --> 35:13.492
NOW, LET'S GO OVER
SOME GROUND RULES.

35:13.492 --> 35:17.196
FIRST, THOSE OFF-SHELF HORMONE
TREATMENTS YOU'RE TAKING --

35:17.196 --> 35:19.117
NO.
THOSE ARE OVER.

35:19.117 --> 35:21.370
FROM NOW ON, EVERYTHING
THAT GOES IN YOUR BODY

35:21.370 --> 35:24.293
IS APPROVED AND REGULATED
BY THIS HOSPITAL.

35:24.293 --> 35:25.374
UNDERSTOOD?

35:26.245 --> 35:27.416
ABSOLUTELY.

35:27.416 --> 35:29.248
OKAY.

35:29.248 --> 35:31.170
YOU SEE A THERAPIST?

35:31.170 --> 35:32.461
NOT FOR A WHILE.

35:32.461 --> 35:35.344
OKAY.
WELL, IT'S TIME TO START AGAIN.

35:35.344 --> 35:38.637
SO, WE'LL GET STARTED
WITH A FULL MEDICAL HISTORY.

35:38.637 --> 35:40.469
YOU KNOW,
I USED TO BE FUN.

35:40.469 --> 35:43.522
I USED TO SKATE AROUND THE HALLS
OF THIS HOSPITAL.

35:43.522 --> 35:45.184
WHY DON'T YOU?

35:45.184 --> 35:46.645
OOPS.

35:46.645 --> 35:48.187
MY BAD.

35:48.187 --> 35:50.148
I USED TO GO DANCING.

35:50.148 --> 35:51.069
I USED TO...

35:51.069 --> 35:52.651
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

35:52.651 --> 35:55.113
...FLIRT
AND BE FLIRTED WITH.

35:55.113 --> 35:58.076
NOW I LIVE IN A HOUSE
FULL OF NAKED PEOPLE

35:58.076 --> 36:00.579
AND ALL OF MY FRIENDS
ARE HER FRIENDS,

36:00.579 --> 36:02.911
AND ALL I HAVE IS WORK
AND I NEVER WANT TO GO HOME.

36:02.911 --> 36:06.335
MM.
I HAD A BUSY, BUSY LIFE.

36:06.335 --> 36:09.127
I SAT ON
ALL THESE BOARDS --

36:09.127 --> 36:11.129
PACIFIC BALLET,
SEATTLE OPERA.

36:11.129 --> 36:15.294
WHATEVER WAS VERY IMPORTANT
TO MY EX.

36:15.294 --> 36:18.757
USED TO BE SO WORRIED
ABOUT WHAT HE THOUGHT OF ME,

36:18.757 --> 36:21.930
WHAT MY PEERS THOUGHT,
WHAT EVERYBODY THOUGHT.

36:21.930 --> 36:26.685
BUT NOW I DO WHAT I WANT,
WHEN I WANT, AND IT'S SWEET.

36:26.685 --> 36:28.016
I HAVE TO TELL YOU,
ROBBINS,

36:28.016 --> 36:31.940
MY LIFE IS SO MUCH BETTER
NOW THAT I HAVE NOTHING.

36:31.940 --> 36:34.443
I MEAN,
I CAN'T RECOMMEND A TUMOR,

36:34.443 --> 36:37.115
BUT YOU SHOULD TRY IT.

36:40.279 --> 36:42.080
YOU SHOULD GO HOME.

36:42.080 --> 36:43.742
I AM HOME.

36:43.742 --> 36:45.534
WHY DO YOU THINK
I STOLE THIS COUCH?

36:45.534 --> 36:46.915
WE CAN'T WASTE A MINUTE.

36:46.915 --> 36:50.539
I'M GONNA STAY HERE
UNTIL, UH...

36:50.539 --> 36:52.501
UNTIL IT'S OVER.

36:52.501 --> 36:55.093
WHATEVER THAT MEANS.

36:57.756 --> 36:59.928
THEN I'LL STAY WITH YOU
TONIGHT.

37:02.050 --> 37:04.052
YOU SHOULD KNOW...

37:04.052 --> 37:05.684
I'M NOT GONNA HAVE SEX
WITH YOU.

37:05.684 --> 37:07.846
SH-SHUT UP!

37:07.846 --> 37:08.807
Y--

37:08.807 --> 37:10.769
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

37:16.985 --> 37:18.697
UH, HI.

37:18.697 --> 37:21.159
HEY. SORRY.

37:21.159 --> 37:22.200
DO YOU DRINK WINE?

37:22.200 --> 37:23.492
UH...

37:23.492 --> 37:25.744
I JUST WANTED TO VISIT,

37:25.744 --> 37:28.577
AND PEOPLE BRING WINE SOMETIMES
WHEN THEY'RE...

37:28.577 --> 37:31.830
♪ AND ALL THE KIDS NOW,
THEY COME RUNNIN' ♪
...GOING TO VISIT
ANOTHER PERSON.

37:31.830 --> 37:35.173
♪ IT'S THE WEEKEND,
IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪
ESPECIALLY IF THEY HAVE --

37:35.173 --> 37:36.675
♪ AND ALL THE PARENTS,
THEY KEEP CALLIN' ♪
THEY BRING A BOTTLE.

37:36.675 --> 37:39.217
♪ BUT THERE'S NO ANSWER ♪
THAT'S -- THAT'S WATER.

37:39.217 --> 37:40.509
SO...

37:40.509 --> 37:41.930
♪ 'CAUSE IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪
BECAUSE I DON'T DRINK WINE.

37:41.930 --> 37:43.592
I -- I DON'T DRINK
AT ALL.

37:43.592 --> 37:44.683
NOT ANYMORE.

37:44.683 --> 37:49.888
SO, I BROUGHT WATER,
AND...

37:51.520 --> 37:53.101
I'M SORRY.

37:53.101 --> 37:54.983
I HAVE LITERALLY NO GAME.

37:54.983 --> 37:55.654
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:02.070 --> 38:05.364
♪ WORKING CLASS TO THE BONE ♪
I SHOULD GO.
IT'S SPARKLING.

38:05.364 --> 38:07.956
♪ AND I KNOW YOU'RE TIRED
OF HEARING IT ♪
MM-HMM.
LIME.

38:07.956 --> 38:10.619
♪ IT'S THE WEEKEND,
IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪
JUST WANTED TO SAY HI.

38:10.619 --> 38:12.120
♪ THIS RIGHT HERE
IS THE D.O. PROLETARIAT ♪

38:12.120 --> 38:13.912
HEY, DO YOU WANT
SOME WATER?

38:13.912 --> 38:15.123
♪ IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪
I --

38:15.123 --> 38:16.174
♪ COME ON THE WEEKEND ♪
NOT THIRSTY.

38:16.174 --> 38:18.417
OKAY, WAIT.

38:18.417 --> 38:20.178
AMELIA.

38:20.178 --> 38:22.180
STOP WALKING.

38:22.180 --> 38:23.762
[ SIGHS ]

38:23.762 --> 38:26.134
♪ AND ALL THE KIDS NOW,
THEY COME RUNNIN' ♪

38:26.134 --> 38:30.098
♪ IT'S THE WEEKEND,
IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪
I'M GONNA KISS YOU NOW,
SO DON'T -- DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

38:30.098 --> 38:32.351
♪ AND ALL THE PARENTS,
THEY KEEP CALLIN' ♪

38:32.351 --> 38:34.102
♪ BUT THERE'S NO ANSWER ♪

38:34.102 --> 38:36.024
♪ 'CAUSE IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪

38:36.024 --> 38:38.697
♪ HELL, YEAH, I JUST GOT PAID ♪

38:38.697 --> 38:42.150
♪ IT'S TIME
TO GET THIS STARTED ♪

38:42.150 --> 38:44.943
♪ WAIT TILL I STAKE MY CLAIM ♪

38:44.943 --> 38:48.116
♪ FORGET THAT
I WAS EVER YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪

38:48.116 --> 38:50.208
♪ TONIGHT I MIGHT
JUST LOSE MY WAY ♪

38:50.208 --> 38:52.411
IT'S SCARY TO REVEAL
EVERYTHING ABOUT OURSELVES.

38:52.411 --> 38:55.003
♪ BUT I'LL NEVER GET
DOWNHEARTED ♪
AND NOW YOU CAN GO HOME.

38:55.003 --> 38:57.796
I'M JUST -- UM -- NOW I'M
GONNA -- I'M GONNA GO HOME.

38:57.796 --> 39:01.129
♪ FORGET THAT
I WAS EVER YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪

39:01.960 --> 39:04.172
Which is...that way.

39:09.888 --> 39:13.021
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

39:13.021 --> 39:16.064
♪ AND ALL THE KIDS NOW,
THEY COME RUNNIN' ♪

39:16.064 --> 39:18.977
♪ IT'S THE WEEKEND,
IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪

39:18.977 --> 39:22.190
♪ AND ALL THE PARENTS,
THEY KEEP CALLIN' ♪

39:22.190 --> 39:24.032
♪ BUT THERE'S NO ANSWER ♪

39:24.032 --> 39:25.784
♪ 'CAUSE IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪

39:25.784 --> 39:28.987
♪ HELL, YEAH,
I JUST GOT PAID ♪

39:28.987 --> 39:32.290
♪ IT'S TIME
TO GET THIS STARTED ♪
FEAR MAKES US
HOLD OURSELVES BACK.

39:32.290 --> 39:34.993
♪ WAIT TILL I STAKE MY CLAIM ♪
IS THAT SO WRONG?

39:34.993 --> 39:36.455
♪ FORGET THAT I WAS EVER
YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪
Man: HERE YOU GO.

39:36.455 --> 39:38.547
OKAY,
THIS IS TAKING TOO LONG.

39:38.547 --> 39:41.379
♪ TONIGHT, I MIGHT JUST LOSE
MY WAY ♪
DANCE WITH ME.

39:41.379 --> 39:43.051
♪ BUT I'LL NEVER GET
DOWNHEARTED ♪
OKAY.

39:43.051 --> 39:44.423
OKAY.

39:44.423 --> 39:47.305
♪ GOOD FRIENDS
KEEP ENEMIES AT BAY ♪

39:47.305 --> 39:50.098
♪ FORGET THAT I WAS EVER
YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪

39:50.098 --> 39:51.640
MAYBE. PROBABLY.

39:51.640 --> 39:54.062
♪ TONIGHT,
I MIGHT JUST LOSE MY WAY ♪

39:54.062 --> 39:56.435
♪ BUT I'LL NEVER GET
DOWNHEARTED ♪

39:56.435 --> 39:58.146
♪ GOOD FRIENDS KEEP ENEMIES
AT BAY ♪
OH. [ LAUGHS ]

39:58.146 --> 40:00.148
BUT STILL...
Shh.

40:00.148 --> 40:02.441
♪ FORGET THAT I WAS EVER
YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪
...IT HELPS
TO BE A LITTLE SNEAKY,

40:02.441 --> 40:04.483
A LITTLE PROTECTIVE.

40:09.528 --> 40:13.622
IT'S NOT SAFE TO JUST BLURT OUT
ALL OF OUR SECRETS.

40:13.622 --> 40:16.745
NEVER GOT ON THE PLANE.
I NEVER WENT TO D.C.

40:16.745 --> 40:19.167
NOW YOU WANT TO BLAB.

40:19.167 --> 40:20.128
WHERE'S PIERCE?

40:20.128 --> 40:23.592
WHAT IS SHE -- MORNING SHIFT?
I GET NIGHTS?

40:23.592 --> 40:26.094
I WENT TO A HOTEL.

40:26.094 --> 40:28.927
♪ WORKING CLASS TO THE BONE,
AND I KNOW YOU'RE TIRED... ♪
WHAT?
WITH WHO? DO I KNOW HIM?

40:28.927 --> 40:30.759
NO. BY MYSELF.

40:30.759 --> 40:32.350
♪ IT'S THE WEEKEND,
IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪
YOU DIDN'T WANT TO
SEE DEREK?

40:32.350 --> 40:35.764
♪ THIS RIGHT HERE
IS THE D.O. PROLETARIAT ♪
I DID.
TOO MUCH.

40:35.764 --> 40:40.148
♪ IT'S THE WEEKEND,
COME ON THE WEEKEND ♪
WHAT IF I GOT OFF THE PLANE
AND HE WASN'T HAPPY TO SEE ME?

40:40.148 --> 40:42.320
WHAT IF HE DIDN'T SMILE?

40:42.320 --> 40:43.692
THAT WOULD BE BAD.

40:43.692 --> 40:45.484
THAT WOULD MEAN IT'S DONE,
IT'S OVER.

40:47.445 --> 40:50.989
SO WHAT?
YOU JUST HEAD OUT ALONE?

40:50.989 --> 40:52.831
I MEAN,
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST COME BACK?

40:52.831 --> 40:54.833
♪ AND ALL THE KIDS NOW,
THEY COME RUNNIN' ♪
I WAS GOING TO.

40:54.833 --> 40:57.455
♪ IT'S THE WEEKEND,
IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪
AND THEN...I DIDN'T.

40:57.455 --> 41:00.499
♪ AND ALL THE PARENTS,
THEY KEEP CALLIN' ♪

41:00.499 --> 41:01.960
♪ BUT THERE'S NO ANSWER ♪

41:01.960 --> 41:04.172
♪ 'CAUSE IT'S THE WEEKEND ♪
AND IT WAS AMAZING.

41:04.172 --> 41:06.464
♪ HELL, YEAH,
I JUST GOT PAID ♪

41:06.464 --> 41:10.929
♪ IT'S TIME
TO GET THIS STARTED ♪
IT WAS JUST ME
FOR THREE DAYS.

41:10.929 --> 41:13.552
♪ WAIT TILL I STAKE MY CLAIM ♪
ALL BY MYSELF.

41:13.552 --> 41:16.394
♪ FORGET THAT I WAS EVER
YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪
I WASN'T ANYBODY'S WIFE
OR DOCTOR OR MOTHER.

41:16.394 --> 41:18.557
♪ TONIGHT,
I MIGHT JUST LOSE MY WAY ♪

41:18.557 --> 41:20.148
AND I KIND OF LIKED IT.

41:20.148 --> 41:22.310
♪ BUT I'LL NEVER GET
DOWNHEARTED ♪
[ LAUGHS ]

41:22.310 --> 41:24.813
♪ GOOD FRIENDS
KEEP ENEMIES AT BAY ♪

41:24.813 --> 41:27.235
♪ FORGET THAT I WAS EVER
YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪
IF I HAD GONE TO D.C.,
WE WOULD'VE FOUGHT

41:27.235 --> 41:29.608
OR WE WOULD'VE TALKED
ABOUT FIGHTING,

41:29.608 --> 41:31.950
♪ HELL, YEAH,
I JUST GOT PAID ♪
AND I DON'T WANT TO TALK
ANYMORE.

41:31.950 --> 41:34.032
♪ IT'S TIME
TO GET THIS STARTED ♪
I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT
ANYMORE.

41:34.032 --> 41:35.574
[ SIGHS ] ALEX.

41:35.574 --> 41:37.415
♪ WAIT TILL I STAKE MY CLAIM ♪

41:37.415 --> 41:41.209
♪ FORGET THAT I WAS EVER
YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪
I DON'T WANT TO
LEAVE HIM.

41:41.209 --> 41:46.124
♪ TONIGHT, I MIGHT JUST LOSE
MY WAY ♪
BUT I DEFINITELY DO NOT WANT TO
BE WITH HIM RIGHT NOW.

41:46.124 --> 41:49.127
♪ BUT I'LL NEVER GET
DOWNHEARTED ♪
WE CAN'T JUST
LAY ALL THE TRUTH OUT THERE...

41:49.127 --> 41:51.840
♪ GOOD FRIENDS KEEP ENEMIES
AT BAY ♪
...EXPOSE OURSELVES TO GOD
AND EVERYBODY.

41:51.840 --> 41:54.012
♪ FORGET THAT I WAS EVER
YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪
HEY,
HAVE YOU SEEN MY -- OH!

41:54.012 --> 41:56.635
♪ HELL, YEAH,
I JUST GOT PAID ♪
OH. A LITTLE WARNING...

41:56.635 --> 41:58.977
♪ IT'S TIME
TO GET THIS STARTED ♪
...WHEN PEOPLE
ARE OVER WOULD BE NICE.

41:58.977 --> 42:00.689
I TOLD HER TO WEAR PANTS.

42:00.689 --> 42:02.731
♪ TONIGHT, I MIGHT JUST LOSE
MY WAY ♪
I DON'T HAVE TO WEAR PANTS.

42:02.731 --> 42:05.103
♪ BUT I'LL NEVER GET
DOWNHEARTED ♪
IT'S PERFECTLY FINE
IF I DON'T WEAR PANTS.

42:05.103 --> 42:06.404
DOESN'T MAKE ME STUPID.

42:06.404 --> 42:08.106
'CAUSE ONCE THE TRUTH
IS OUT...

42:08.106 --> 42:10.068
I'M GONNA MARRY
THAT GIRL.

42:10.068 --> 42:12.490
♪ FORGET THAT I WAS EVER
YOUR WHIPPING BOY ♪
...WE HAVE TO FACE IT
OURSELVES.

42:12.490 --> 42:14.282
[ SIGHS ]

42:14.282 --> 42:17.155
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN WITH US.
